</media:description><media:credit>The Action Lab</media:credit></media:content></item><item><guid isPermaLink="false">1659950948681116sg</guid><title>Why electrified drops resist splashing</title><link>https://www.facebook.com/reel/1659950948681116/</link><pubDate>Sat, 16 May 2026 01:00:00 GMT</pubDate><description>Electrified drops do not splash upon impacting a surface because the electrostatic charge creates an attraction between the drop and the surface, which suppresses the outward spreading that creates a splash.</description><media:thumbnail url="https://storage.googleapis.com/trendly_facebook_videos/461822001292778/1659950948681116.jpg" /><media:content url="https://storage.googleapis.com/trendly_facebook_videos/461822001292778/1659950948681116.mp4" type="video/mp4" medium="video" duration="188"><media:title>Why electrified drops resist splashing</media:title><media:description>Electrified drops do not splash upon impacting a surface because the electrostatic charge creates an attraction between the drop and the surface, which suppresses the outward spreading that creates a splash.</media:description><media:credit>The Action Lab</media:credit></media:content></item></channel></rss>